      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 122: 🔴 Critical Issues - `removeCallbacks()` only removes queued callbacks; it cannot stop a `deactivateRunnable` that has already started on the main looper. Because `lastPushTime`/`lastCallPushTime` are updated only inside the later posted block, a background push arriving exactly as the runnable starts can still be evaluated with stale timestamps and enqueue account deactivation before the restore/reconnect path, which can drop an incoming call negotiation. Make the grace-window timestamp visible before attempting to cancel the runnable, and read it atomically from the runnable.\n\n```suggestion\nprivate val lastPushTime \u003d AtomicLong(0L)\nprivate val lastCallPushTime \u003d AtomicLong(0L)\n\n// in deactivateRunnable\nval graceRemaining \u003d maxOf(\n    lastCallPushTime.get() + CALL_PUSH_GRACE_MS,\n    lastPushTime.get() + PUSH_GRACE_MS\n) - now\n\n// in onBackgroundPushReceived\nval now \u003d SystemClock.elapsedRealtime()\nlastPushTime.set(now)\nif (isCallPush) lastCallPushTime.set(now)\nbackgroundHandler.removeCallbacks(deactivateRunnable)\nbackgroundHandler.post {\n    mAccountService.restoreProxyAccountsAfterBackground()\n    if (triggerReconnect) hardwareService.connectivityChanged(true)\n    backgroundHandler.removeCallbacks(deactivateRunnable)\n    backgroundHandler.postDelayed(deactivateRunnable, BACKGROUND_DEACTIVATION_DELAY_MS)\n}\n```",
