      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T13:24:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The restored-active state is the correct contract here, not a leak. When push is disabled there is no FCM wakeup path: deactivating accounts (or leaving them inactive) would make the user unreachable for incoming calls/messages — exactly the merge-blocking issue raised on PS20 (comment on JamiApplicationFirebase:132) that PS22 fixed by restoring on this very transition. Persistent background connections with push off is the pre-patch, user-opted behavior for every non-push configuration; the battery optimization only applies while FCM can substitute for those connections. Note also the restored set is almost always empty on this path: settings changes happen in the foreground, where onStart already restored and cleared it — the non-empty case is precisely the race this ordering protects (restore queued FIFO before setProxyEnabled(false) so it still sees the proxy enabled and does not drop the ids as terminal).",
